  "prompt": "What are some alternatives to yelp in India?",
  "response": "Yelp isn't as popular in India as it is in other countries. Here are some popular alternatives to Yelp in India, categorized for easier browsing:\n\n**1. Comprehensive Listing & Review Platforms:**\n\n*   **Zomato:** Primarily known for restaurant reviews and listings, but it's expanding to include nightlife, events, and other categories. It has a strong focus on food photography and user ratings. Very popular in India.\n*   **Dineout:** Another major player in the restaurant discovery and booking space. Offers restaurant deals, discounts, and reservation features.\n*   **Justdial:** A long-established directory service that lists businesses across a wide range of categories, including restaurants, shops, services, and professionals. Includes user reviews and ratings. While not as modern as some others, it has a large and established database.\n*   **Sulekha:** Similar to Justdial but also offers classifieds and allows users to connect with service providers for various needs.  Includes reviews and ratings.\n\n**2. Google Maps:**\n\n*   **Google Maps:** Though not strictly a review platform, Google Maps is heavily used for finding businesses, getting directions, and reading reviews.  Many Indian businesses rely on their Google My Business profile and encourage customers to leave reviews there.  Its wide adoption makes it a key source of information.\n\n**3. Niche Platforms & Social Media:**\n\n*   **Instagram:**  Increasingly used for discovering and reviewing businesses, especially restaurants and cafes. People share photos and stories, and hashtags make it easy to find places.\n*   **Facebook:** Businesses often have Facebook pages where customers can leave reviews and comments. Facebook groups can also be a good source of recommendations.\n*   **TripAdvisor:** While not specifically focused on India, TripAdvisor is a well-known platform for travel-related reviews, including hotels, restaurants, and attractions.\n\n**4. Local Recommendations:**\n\n*   **Word-of-Mouth:** In India, word-of-mouth recommendations are still very influential. Asking friends, family, and colleagues for their opinions is a common practice.\n*   **Local Blogs & Influencers:** Many local bloggers and social media influencers focus on reviewing businesses in specific cities or regions. These can provide valuable insights and personalized recommendations.\n\n**Factors to Consider When Choosing an Alternative:**\n\n*   **Focus:** Some platforms are primarily focused on restaurants (Zomato, Dineout), while others cover a broader range of businesses (Justdial, Sulekha, Google Maps).\n*   **Location:** Some platforms may have stronger coverage in certain cities or regions than others.\n*   **Features:** Consider the features you need, such as booking options, deals, or the ability to see user photos.\n*   **Trustworthiness:**  Be mindful of fake or biased reviews. Look for platforms with strong moderation policies and a history of reliable reviews.\n\nIn conclusion, while Yelp isn't a major player in India, there are plenty of effective alternatives for discovering and reviewing local businesses. Zomato, Google Maps, Justdial, and Dineout are some of the most popular options, but the best choice will depend on your specific needs and preferences.  Don't underestimate the power of word-of-mouth and local influencers!\n",
